NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

assign(uint256).notice: Assigns smart contract to existing NFT. That NFT will collect fees generated by the smart contract.         Callable only by smart contract itself.

currentCounterId().notice: Returns current value of counter used to tokenId of new minted NFTs

distributeFees(uint256).notice: Distributes collected fees to the smart contract. Only callable by owner.

feeRecipient(address).notice: maps smart contract address to tokenId

getTokenId(address).notice: Returns tokenId that collects fees generated by the smart contract

isRegistered(address).notice: Returns true if smart contract is registered to collect fees

register(address).notice: Mints ownership NFT that allows the owner to collect fees earned by the smart contract.         `msg.sender` is assumed to be a smart contract that earns fees. Only smart contract itself         can register a fee receipient.

withdraw(uint256,address,uint256).notice: Withdraws earned fees to `_recipient` address. Only callable by NFT owner.
